        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 5:14PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Salem, or 15 miles northeast of Rusk, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rusk, Alto, Sacul, New Salem, Ponta, Douglass, Trawick, New
Summerfield, Cushing, Mount Enterprise, Gallatin, Reklaw, Lilbert,
Looneyville, Glenfawn, Linwood, Laneville and Brachfield.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
